  <original-body>ActionView::Helpers::TranslationHelper.translate in edge calls html_safe! on the return value of I18n.translate regardless of what type it is.

This makes using arrays impossible, because they don't respond to html_safe!. Arrays are used in the &quot;standard&quot; locale files by Sven Fuchs e.a. for day_names, month_names etc.

A simple workaround is this:
@@@ ruby
class Array
        def html_safe!
                each {|e| e.html_safe!  unless e.nil? }
        end
end
@@@</original-body>
